The paper discusses the design of backdoor attacks in sequential decision-making agents, which involves machine learning techniques such as reinforcement learning and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses potential approaches to defend against or detect such attacks, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and neural networks (cs.NE).
